      "content": "Feeling that your body has become a hollow vessel without an internal identity is a terrifying experience when your mind no longer connects with your physical form. While this perspective of being biologically disconnected is painfully real, it is important to know that cognitive painkillers can sometimes cut off part of the brain from painkillers, not painkillers themselves. Please consider reaching out to a suicide prevention hotline, as they can help guide you through this phase of feeling like you don't exist.",
